      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:7:16:5",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " مَنْ شَرِبَ مِنَ الْخَمْرِ شَرْبَةً لَمْ يَقْبَلِ اللَّهُ مِنْهُ صَلَاةً أَرْبَعِينَ يَوْماً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Abu Ali Al Ashary, from Muhammad Bin Abdul Jabbar, from Safwan, from Al A’ala, from Muhammad Bin Muslim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from one of the two (5th or 6th Imam<sup>asws</sup>) having said: ‘The one who drinks from the wine a drink, a Prayer would not be Accepted from him for forty days’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "5. Abu Ali al-Ash‘ariy has narrated from Muhammad ibn ‘Abd al-Jabbar from Safwan from al-‘Ala’ from Muhammad ibn Muslim who has said the following: “One of the two Imam, (abu Ja‘far or abu ‘Abd Allah), ‘Alayhim al-Salam, has said, ‘If one drinks one sip of wine his Salat (prayer) is not accepted forty days.’” "
        ]
      }
